      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> the chamberlain whose treason opened Scarwall to Mandraivus — and who, denied his promised reward, drowned the hero's sword in the Sacred Lake (H3–H4) and fed. Five centuries of guilt and hunger made him a <strong>pharmakos</strong>: an 80-foot worm of scapegoated sin coiled around <strong>Serithtial</strong> itself. The campaign's last gate before the sword.</p>",
